ekhon nedekha nodir xhipare ( assamese : এখন নেদেখা নদীৰ সিপাৰে , english : on the other bank of the unseen river ) is a 2012 assamese language socio-political thriller film , with some dialogue in hindi , starring sanjay suri and bidita bag in the lead roles . it was directed by bidyut kotoky and produced by national film development corporation of india . the film was simultaneously made in hindi as as the river flows . the story was inspired by the kidnapping of activist sanjoy ghosh , who was first abducted in 1997 from the island majuli in assam supposed to be by the united liberation front of asom ( ulfa ) and subsequently killed . a controversy developed when it got rejected by the jury of the 59th national film awards in the category of best assamese film for being " not assamese " .